Estimate parameters

Source: R/estimation.R
estimate_parameters.Rd

Given existing survey data, this function estimates the parameters of the latent variables.

estimate_parameters(data, n_levels, skew = 0)

Arguments

data

The survey responses where the columns correspond to individual items. Apart from this, `data` can be of almost any class such as "data.frame" "matrix" or "array".

n_levels

The number of response categories, a vector or a number.

skew

Marginal skewness of latent variables, defaults to 0.

Value

A table of estimated parameters for each latent variable.

See also

See also [latent2likert::estimate_mean_and_sd()].
